Metadata: Careers in Science: Selene Fregosi (Webinar held October 21, 2020)
Growing Engineers and Marine Scientists Webinar, October 21, 2020
Oregon Sea Grant; Published on YouTube November 2, 2020

This webinar career series is for middle and high school students. Postdoctoral researcher, Selene Fregosi talks about how she uses underwater microphones to record whale sounds, locate them and study how  noise pollution affects them.
